<p style="text-align: left;">The audition of 10-15 minutes should include repertoire similar to that listed below (<em>memory required</em>).</p>
<p style="text-align: left;">Repertoire should be representative of at least 3 of the 4 categories:</p>
<ol>
<li>Bach, Two Part Inventions, Preludes and Fugues</li>
<li>Sonatas of appropriate difficulty by Beethoven, Haydn, and Mozart, such as Beethoven, Op. 10 No. 1; Haydn, Sonata in E minor, H. XVI:34; Mozart, Sonata in G major, K. 283</li>
<li>Mendelssohn, Songs without Words; Chopin: easier Nocturnes and Waltzes, Mazurkas, Preludes</li>
<li>Bartok: Mikrokosmos Vol. 6</li>
</ol>
<p>On-campus auditions will be held January 23-24, 2014.</p>
<p>Satellite auditions will be held in Salt Lake City on January 25, 2014 at the&nbsp;LDS Stake Center, 142 West 200 North,&nbsp;Salt Lake City, UT 84116 from&nbsp;9:00a.m. to 3:00p.m. For more information and to schedule an audition, please contact <a href="x44712.xml" title="Stephen Thomas" target="_blank">Stephen Thomas</a>.</p>
